lamington
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number:
Definition:a sponge square covered with chocolate icing and coconut; later occas. with jelly and coconut; possibly earlier used of the sponge itself
Origin:[none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain:[none]
Region:[none]
See:also lamington cake
Pronunciation:
Notes: prob. f. Baron Lamington, Governor of Queensland (1895-1901); also (misspelt) le(m)minton, leamington
